{
  "texts": [
    "Heart disease refers to any condition that impairs the heart's capacity to function normally.",
    "In recent years, CVD has become the leading cause of death in the world.",
    "Congestive heart failure (CHF) prevalence is expected to rise by 46% by 2030 compared to 2012 rates 1.",
    "The incidence and mortality rates of CVD can be significantly lowered by diagnosing the problem, according to research, in both patients who are already aware of their condition and those who are not 2.",
    "Early detection and diagnosis can result in prompt interventions and suitable therapies, which can enhance patient outcomes and lower the chance of problems."
  ]
}